    <h2>1.2 - Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD)</h2>
    <div class="erd-description">
      <p>My application uses a relational database with the following relationships:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Users have many Reviews</li>
        <li>A Recipe has many Reviews.</li>
        <li>A User has many favorite_recipes (where is_favorite=true).</li>
        <li>A Recipe has many users who reviewed/favorited it.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="erd-visual">
      <pre>
      +------------------+       +------------------+       +------------------+
      |      User        |       |      Review      |       |      Recipe      |
      +------------------+       +------------------+       +------------------+
      | id (PK)          |------>| user_id (FK)     |       | id (PK)          |
      | username         |       | recipe_id (FK)   |<------| title            |
      | email            |       | rating           |       | cooking_time     |
      | created_at       |       | comment          |       | ingredients_list |
      | updated_at       |       | is_favorite      |       | dietary_labels   |
      +------------------+       | created_at       |       | image_url        |
            |                    | updated_at       |       | created_at       |
            |                    +------------------+       | updated_at       |
            |                                              +------------------+
            |                                                    ^
            |                                                    |
            +----------------------------------------------------+
      </pre>
    </div>
  </section>
